WEBVTT

00:02.580 --> 00:04.290
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:04.290 --> 00:05.750
I have been thinking about
maybe performing again,

00:05.750 --> 00:06.670
getting back on stage.

00:06.670 --> 00:07.880
I thought you
gave that all up, man.

00:07.880 --> 00:09.580
Yeah, so did I.

00:09.580 --> 00:11.540
Gary:
I will do whatever it takes
to get you well,

00:11.540 --> 00:13.040
and we will fight this thing
together.

00:13.040 --> 00:14.330
I'm done with treatment.

00:14.330 --> 00:16.250
I'm not gonna fight
my cancer.

00:16.250 --> 00:18.540
Rome: If you hadn't called
to tell me about Jon,

00:18.540 --> 00:19.920
I would be dead right now.

00:19.920 --> 00:22.040
I quit my job
to pursue my dreams.

00:22.040 --> 00:24.540
I thought I'd feel different.
I don't.

00:24.540 --> 00:27.380
Dr. Heller:
I am gonna start you on
an antidepressant.

00:27.380 --> 00:29.330
I can't be with you
anymore.

00:29.330 --> 00:30.670
Eddie: I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

00:30.670 --> 00:32.120
My couch is your couch.

00:32.120 --> 00:33.420
As long as you need it.

00:33.420 --> 00:34.750
Rome: I know that
you're pregnant.

00:34.750 --> 00:35.670
I saw the stick.

00:35.670 --> 00:37.250
It's Delilah's.

00:37.250 --> 00:40.500
♪♪

00:40.500 --> 00:42.790
Rome: Normally,
I look forward to game night,

00:42.790 --> 00:44.920
but I don't know.

00:44.920 --> 00:46.330
Tonight feels like
the finals.

00:46.330 --> 00:47.580
The biggest game
is going to be

00:47.580 --> 00:49.880
not letting anyone else know
that Delilah is pregnant.

00:49.880 --> 00:51.540
We are
in the Thunderdome here.

00:51.540 --> 00:53.290
Babe, I need you...

00:53.290 --> 00:54.250
No.
...to lie.

00:54.250 --> 00:55.210
No.
Rome.

00:55.210 --> 00:56.120
No!
Rome.

00:56.120 --> 00:58.790
No! No.
Look at me.

00:58.790 --> 00:59.830
You're a writer.

00:59.830 --> 01:01.210
Make up a story.

01:01.210 --> 01:02.330
I need context, okay?

01:02.330 --> 01:03.880
I need --
I need motivation.

01:03.880 --> 01:05.000
I need backstory.

01:05.000 --> 01:07.330
I believe there is
sufficient backstory here.

01:07.330 --> 01:09.080
Wait. [ Sighs ]

01:09.080 --> 01:11.080
Rome, I'm serious.

01:11.080 --> 01:12.960
Not a word of this to the guys
or anyone.

01:12.960 --> 01:15.670
I still can't believe

01:15.670 --> 01:17.670
you didn't ask Delilah
who the father was.

01:17.670 --> 01:19.620
Montel Williams
made an entire career

01:19.620 --> 01:20.540
off of that question.

01:20.540 --> 01:21.540
How could you not ask?

01:21.540 --> 01:22.710
[ Sighs ]

01:22.710 --> 01:23.880
Because she's my friend.

01:23.880 --> 01:25.500
♪ Let me slip through ♪

01:25.500 --> 01:27.620
And if she wanted to tell me,
she would.

01:27.620 --> 01:29.460
[ Doorbell rings ]
♪ I'm just tryna
move up front ♪

01:29.460 --> 01:31.250
Early?

01:31.250 --> 01:32.620
Who comes to game night
early?

01:32.620 --> 01:34.960
People who do not know
Delilah is pregnant.

01:34.960 --> 01:36.290
Okay, o-okay, can --

01:36.290 --> 01:37.670
can we just go over
what everyone knows?

01:37.670 --> 01:39.330
So, Eddie and Gary
think that you're pregnant.

01:39.330 --> 01:40.540
[ Sighing ]
Oh, thank you, Big Man.

01:40.540 --> 01:42.120
Okay, and Delilah --
What does Delilah know?

01:42.120 --> 01:43.330
Delilah knows
she's pregnant.

01:43.330 --> 01:44.920
She is the one
who is pregnant.
Right.

01:44.920 --> 01:46.380
So --
So, what about Maggie?

01:46.380 --> 01:47.920
What does Maggie know?
Nothing.

01:47.920 --> 01:49.670
God,
I wish I was Maggie.

01:49.670 --> 01:51.210
Hi!
Hey!

01:51.210 --> 01:53.330
Hey, I know we're early.
I'm sorry.

01:53.330 --> 01:55.080
But I love a good game night.
I love it.

01:55.080 --> 01:56.170
Rome: How about I get
that jacket from you?
Oh, thank you.

01:56.170 --> 01:57.170
A little heads-up --

01:57.170 --> 01:59.290
this one
is super competitive.

01:59.290 --> 02:02.420
Uh, a little heads-up --
this one is going down.

02:02.420 --> 02:03.750
A little heads-up --

02:03.750 --> 02:05.040
this is what the entire
car ride over was like.

02:05.040 --> 02:06.710
Gary: Oh, really,
'cause if memory serves,

02:06.710 --> 02:08.080
the whole car ride over

02:08.080 --> 02:10.920
was you freaking out
about your gig.
Rome: Gig?

02:10.920 --> 02:13.670
Our boy here booked himself
a solo show.

02:13.670 --> 02:15.000
Getting back on stage.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.080
I'm just the opener.

02:17.080 --> 02:18.460
Okay,
enough about the flyers.

02:18.460 --> 02:19.920
Let's get
into some games.

02:19.920 --> 02:22.120
"I, Tonya"
does not have a car.

02:22.120 --> 02:23.830
John Mayer
is my new roommate.

02:23.830 --> 02:25.750
How great is my life?

02:25.750 --> 02:26.500
Maggie: Mm-hmm.

02:26.500 --> 02:27.540
Gina.

02:27.540 --> 02:28.670
Oh.

02:28.670 --> 02:29.710
Oh, you know what?

02:29.710 --> 02:32.040
I'm gonna take that.

02:32.040 --> 02:33.710
You hate wine.
What are you doing?

02:33.710 --> 02:35.540
Gary: Not tonight, I don't.
It's game night.

02:35.540 --> 02:37.040
In fact, give me that.

02:37.040 --> 02:38.420
I'm gonna
double-fist the vin.

02:38.420 --> 02:39.790
Huh? What do you think of that?
Look at me.

02:39.790 --> 02:42.040
[ Doorbell rings ]
Oh.

02:42.040 --> 02:43.040
All right,
I'll probably take one.

02:43.040 --> 02:44.620
Here, take this one.

02:44.620 --> 02:46.000
I can't.

02:46.000 --> 02:48.540
I just started
taking antidepressants.

02:48.540 --> 02:49.750
[ Glasses clink ]

02:49.750 --> 02:51.620
♪♪

02:51.620 --> 02:52.920
Hey.
Hey!

02:52.920 --> 02:55.670
Maggie: Hi!
Gary: Good evening, D.

02:55.670 --> 02:58.040
These are beautiful.
I poured you a glass.

02:58.040 --> 03:00.080
Ah --
No, wait! Whoa.

03:01.830 --> 03:03.000
She just got here.

03:03.000 --> 03:04.830
The wine and the people
need to breathe.

03:04.830 --> 03:06.790
♪♪

03:06.790 --> 03:08.170
Oh, my good Lord.

03:08.170 --> 03:09.500
Yeah, none for me.

03:09.500 --> 03:11.250
I need a clear mind
for game night.

03:11.250 --> 03:13.170
Oh, she's on my team.

03:13.170 --> 03:14.670
Maggie:
Okay, who else is good?

03:16.290 --> 03:17.420
[ Whispering ] What?
Small problem.

03:17.420 --> 03:19.120
Yeah?

03:19.120 --> 03:20.830
Rome found
the pregnancy test.

03:20.830 --> 03:21.960
He thought it was mine.

03:21.960 --> 03:23.080
[ Exhaling ]
Oh, thank God.

03:23.080 --> 03:25.290
So, I had to tell him
it was yours.

03:25.290 --> 03:27.120
Oh, God.

03:27.120 --> 03:29.250
Okay, so you don't want
something Biblical.

03:29.250 --> 03:31.960
How about Storm?

03:31.960 --> 03:33.080
No, Storm is not a name.

03:33.080 --> 03:34.460
It's a weather alert.

03:34.460 --> 03:35.960
Gary, you can't shoot down
all of my ideas

03:35.960 --> 03:37.380
if you're not gonna offer
an alt.

03:37.380 --> 03:39.750
Why don't we let baby daddy
weigh in here?

03:39.750 --> 03:42.330
Is your daughter
gonna be named Storm or no?

03:42.330 --> 03:43.620
Daughter?
Who said daughter?

03:43.620 --> 03:45.080
[ Gasps ]
We didn't.
No, we didn't.

03:45.080 --> 03:46.420
It's a boy.
Dude, boys are the best.

03:46.420 --> 03:47.710
Who's playing catch?
Okay, okay, guys.

03:47.710 --> 03:48.920
Gary: This dude!
Knock it off, okay?

03:48.920 --> 03:50.460
Who's gonna have a catch?

03:50.460 --> 03:52.750
This man right --
Gina's not pregnant!

03:52.750 --> 03:53.880
Regina: [ Sighs ]

03:55.500 --> 03:58.120
Well, then,
whose pee did Gary touch?

04:06.500 --> 04:08.380
Can I -- Can I talk to you
for a second?

04:11.080 --> 04:12.120
Um...

04:13.420 --> 04:14.080
Oh, man.

04:19.000 --> 04:22.250
♪♪

04:22.250 --> 04:23.000
[ Clears throat ]

04:28.620 --> 04:29.960
♪♪

04:29.960 --> 04:33.170
♪ I spend all my time ♪

04:33.170 --> 04:35.080
♪ Waiting around for you ♪

04:35.080 --> 04:37.380
Okay, so what did she say?

04:37.380 --> 04:38.500
Whose baby is it?

04:38.500 --> 04:39.880
She didn't ask.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.500
You didn't ask.

04:41.500 --> 04:43.580
Okay, that makes sense.

04:43.580 --> 04:45.210
I mean,
why would you possibly --

04:45.210 --> 04:47.000
Why -- Why -- Why wouldn't
you ask that question?

04:47.000 --> 04:51.290
Because,
let's be honest,

04:51.290 --> 04:53.170
either way,
it's complicated.

04:53.170 --> 04:56.670
♪♪

04:56.670 --> 04:58.210
Eddie: Listen to me,

04:58.210 --> 05:01.330
maybe everything
does happen for a reason.

05:01.330 --> 05:03.170
I mean,
we love each other, D.

05:03.170 --> 05:04.920
We were gonna tell
Jon and Katherine,

05:04.920 --> 05:06.670
and, yes,

05:06.670 --> 05:08.790
I know there are
a ton of reasons

05:08.790 --> 05:11.210
why we can't be together.

05:11.210 --> 05:15.880
Uh, Sophie, Danny, Theo.

05:15.880 --> 05:17.880
But the fact is,
this is our baby.

05:17.880 --> 05:19.710
Stop.

05:19.710 --> 05:21.880
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:21.880 --> 05:24.420
It's Jon's baby.

05:24.420 --> 05:26.500
What about the time
the condom broke?

05:26.500 --> 05:29.380
No, I spoke to my doctor,
and...

05:29.380 --> 05:33.080
I was pregnant
before that.

05:33.080 --> 05:36.420
But I thought
you and Jon weren't...

05:36.420 --> 05:39.210
♪♪

05:39.210 --> 05:41.670
He was my husband.

05:41.670 --> 05:44.040
♪♪

05:44.040 --> 05:46.250
[ Exhales deeply ]

05:46.250 --> 05:49.790
♪♪

05:49.790 --> 05:51.500
All right, I'll do it.

05:51.500 --> 05:52.750
[ Sniffs ]

05:52.750 --> 05:53.790
I will ask --

05:53.790 --> 05:55.420
when the time is right,
of course.

05:55.420 --> 05:56.460
I have a gentle touch.

05:56.460 --> 05:57.790
You really don't.
Regina: Oh, God.

05:57.790 --> 05:59.080
Gary: What does that --
What do you mean?

05:59.080 --> 06:00.120
You could --
[ Door opens ]

06:00.120 --> 06:01.460
Regina:
Hey, gentle touch.

06:01.460 --> 06:04.670
♪ You play the game ♪

06:04.670 --> 06:06.420
Hey, brother.

06:06.420 --> 06:08.290
♪ It's working
on my brain ♪

06:08.290 --> 06:11.710
♪ I'm feelin' strange ♪

06:11.710 --> 06:13.120
♪♪

06:13.120 --> 06:15.080
♪ I know ♪

06:15.080 --> 06:19.120
♪ There's no going back
for me, baby ♪

06:19.120 --> 06:20.330
Sorry, you guys.

06:20.330 --> 06:29.880
♪♪

06:29.880 --> 06:35.460
[ Bear's Den's
"When You Break" plays ]

06:35.460 --> 06:38.830
♪ Spoiled, selfish
little child ♪

06:42.420 --> 06:45.120
♪ Went out to play
out in the wild ♪

06:49.210 --> 06:52.380
♪ I found you
shaking like a leaf ♪

06:54.460 --> 06:55.790
♪ Underneath ♪

06:55.790 --> 06:57.620
Ed, you okay?

06:57.620 --> 06:59.290
♪ Your family tree ♪

06:59.290 --> 07:02.210
I didn't know
that she and Jon...

07:02.210 --> 07:06.170
♪ You could never live
out in the open ♪
...were...still...

07:08.040 --> 07:11.500
♪ Regretting every word
you've spoken ♪

07:17.170 --> 07:21.580
♪♪

07:21.580 --> 07:23.540
[ Yawns, sniffs ]

07:23.540 --> 07:24.920
♪♪

07:24.920 --> 07:26.500
Good morning.
[ Sighs ]

07:26.500 --> 07:27.920
You, uh,
get some sleep?

07:27.920 --> 07:30.920
Oh, I did,
until I didn't.

07:30.920 --> 07:32.210
Just a general announcement.

07:32.210 --> 07:33.540
The walls
in your apartment --

07:33.540 --> 07:35.080
not as thick
as you think they are.

07:35.080 --> 07:36.210
Oh?

07:36.210 --> 07:37.460
[ Maggie sneezes
in distance ]

07:37.460 --> 07:39.210
Bless you!
[ Glass thuds ]

07:39.210 --> 07:40.540
Oh.
[ Clears throat ]

07:40.540 --> 07:43.290
Well, tonight's
the big night, huh?

07:43.290 --> 07:45.670
You all ready
with your set list?

07:45.670 --> 07:49.170
Yeah, I just want to make sure
it's right.

07:51.250 --> 07:53.000
Wowzers, that's a lot of
black ink, man.

07:53.000 --> 07:54.880
You sure you're okay?

07:54.880 --> 07:57.880
Last night,
a lot of stuff went down.

07:57.880 --> 07:58.880
Yeah, I'm -- I'm fine.

07:58.880 --> 07:59.750
I'm perfectly fine.

07:59.750 --> 08:03.290
I just want to get it right.

08:03.290 --> 08:04.920
Why don't I go with you
to soundcheck?

08:04.920 --> 08:07.170
Be just like the old days.

08:07.170 --> 08:09.710
Except I won't have to
"Bodyguard" you through
the exit after the encore.

08:09.710 --> 08:11.830
Okay, that was one time,
and I'm sober now.
Oh, yeah?

08:11.830 --> 08:16.120
Well, I...
will always love you.

08:16.120 --> 08:17.710
What is this?

08:17.710 --> 08:20.290
Almond milk?

08:20.290 --> 08:21.540
What happened to your whole

08:21.540 --> 08:23.830
"it's only milk
if it comes from a cow" stance?

08:23.830 --> 08:26.120
Maggie's lactose intolerant,
Ed.

08:26.120 --> 08:27.710
And there it is.

08:27.710 --> 08:29.080
No, it's nothing there.

08:29.080 --> 08:31.000
I happen to know how Maggie
likes a lot of things,

08:31.000 --> 08:32.420
or were you not
listening?

08:32.420 --> 08:34.170
Oh...did he...

08:34.170 --> 08:35.790
Heard everything.
Yeah.

08:35.790 --> 08:37.080
Eddie:
Every single thing.

08:37.080 --> 08:38.790
Gary:
You know what this means --

08:38.790 --> 08:40.920
shower sex
is back on the table.
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

08:40.920 --> 08:43.540
Maggie: Why is this
such a thing for you?
Because --

08:43.540 --> 08:44.750
It's not as great as you --

08:44.750 --> 08:46.710
Ugh, Katherine just got

08:46.710 --> 08:49.040
a last-minute business trip
out of town.

08:49.040 --> 08:51.000
She needs me
to take Theo tonight.

08:51.000 --> 08:52.880
I got to cancel the gig.
Gary: Absolutely not, Ed.

08:52.880 --> 08:54.380
You're doing this.

08:54.380 --> 08:55.670
I've already committed
to being your roadie.

08:55.670 --> 08:57.790
Plus, if Katherine
can be a working mom,

08:57.790 --> 08:58.880
you can be a working dad.

08:58.880 --> 09:00.580
Hey, I can watch Theo.

09:00.580 --> 09:02.170
Well, I --

09:02.170 --> 09:03.380
Yeah, I'll take him
to my kickboxing class.

09:03.380 --> 09:04.170
It'll be really fun.

09:06.040 --> 09:08.750
Or I'll -- I'll --
We'll feed the ducks.

09:08.750 --> 09:10.710
That's better.

09:10.710 --> 09:12.210
Regina: So, I'm thinking
for the lighting,

09:12.210 --> 09:14.080
one in the center...
Mm-hmm.

09:14.080 --> 09:15.790
...one in the corner,
and then all along
the north wall.

09:15.790 --> 09:17.250
So, you think you can
have the fixtures in

09:17.250 --> 09:18.250
by end of day?

09:18.250 --> 09:20.000
Yeah, absolutely.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.170
Perfect.
Thank you, Jorge.

09:22.170 --> 09:24.040
Oh, and don't forget --
L.E.D.s only.

09:24.040 --> 09:26.790
We are going for
energy efficiency here.

09:26.790 --> 09:27.960
All right, babe.

09:27.960 --> 09:29.880
I have to go see
the fabric guy.

09:29.880 --> 09:32.670
All right, so you just keep
cranking out those pages.

09:32.670 --> 09:34.710
No distractions.

09:34.710 --> 09:36.830
Except for maybe stay on Jorge
a little bit.

09:36.830 --> 09:38.710
I mean, not so much
that it seems like

09:38.710 --> 09:40.330
I asked you
to stay on Jorge.

09:40.330 --> 09:42.710
So write, except for
when I'm spying on Jorge.

09:42.710 --> 09:43.920
Mm-hmm.
Easy.

09:43.920 --> 09:45.500
Love you. Bye.
Love you.

09:47.210 --> 09:49.040
[ Drill whirs ]

09:51.960 --> 09:53.420
[ No audio ]

10:01.670 --> 10:03.710
[ Drill whirs ]

10:08.580 --> 10:10.500
Shelly: [ Muffled ]
Oh, no, no, no, no.

10:10.500 --> 10:12.040
L.E.D.s are too blue.

10:12.040 --> 10:13.250
[ Normal voice ] I don't know
if you know this,

10:13.250 --> 10:14.290
but lighting's important.

10:14.290 --> 10:15.380
Ah!

10:15.380 --> 10:16.500
Trust me.

10:16.500 --> 10:17.960
You'll want
an incandescent feel.

10:17.960 --> 10:19.210
But you --
Please.

10:19.210 --> 10:20.290
[ Gasps ]

10:20.290 --> 10:21.880
Rome!

10:21.880 --> 10:23.380
Oh!
Oh-ho.

10:23.380 --> 10:27.040
Ooh.
Shelly.

10:27.040 --> 10:30.040
So, does Gina
know that you're here?

10:30.040 --> 10:30.960
No, no, no, no.
She doesn't.

10:30.960 --> 10:32.210
Oh, no, please.

10:32.210 --> 10:34.420
I-I want to surprise her.

10:34.420 --> 10:36.120
It would help
if I had my keys.

10:36.120 --> 10:37.750
Hey, Jorge, how come
I don't hear drilling?

10:37.750 --> 10:38.920
[ Chuckles ]

10:41.790 --> 10:42.880
Mom.

10:48.330 --> 10:53.500
♪♪

10:53.500 --> 10:58.880
♪♪

10:58.880 --> 11:00.830
What do you mean denied?

11:00.830 --> 11:02.580
Well, tell them
I want an answer.

11:02.580 --> 11:05.330
My husband's been doing business
with your bank for years.

11:05.330 --> 11:08.290
Th-This is --
This is unacceptable.

11:08.290 --> 11:09.830
Thank you.

11:09.830 --> 11:11.460
[ Telephone beeps ]
[ Sighs ]

11:11.460 --> 11:12.960
So, I canceled

11:12.960 --> 11:14.210
the floral delivery
to the office,

11:14.210 --> 11:16.670
and I forwarded
Jon's work line to my cell.

11:18.710 --> 11:21.880
Which reminds me,
a Barbara Morgan called.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.620
[ Sighs ]

11:23.620 --> 11:25.170
Barbara Morgan?

11:25.170 --> 11:28.750
No, I-I don't know anyone
named Barbara Morgan.

11:28.750 --> 11:32.790
Yeah,
must be a wrong number.

11:32.790 --> 11:36.170
Hey, are you okay?

11:36.170 --> 11:38.420
The loan for the restaurant
just got denied.

11:38.420 --> 11:40.920
Just --
it makes no sense.

11:44.210 --> 11:45.880
Well, maybe because

11:45.880 --> 11:47.880
Regina's last restaurant
went under.

11:47.880 --> 11:50.120
Yeah.

11:50.120 --> 11:51.920
Mm-hmm, maybe. Yeah.

11:53.420 --> 11:54.920
It must be a mistake.

11:54.920 --> 11:56.500
Even when Jon applied
sometimes for loans,

11:56.500 --> 11:58.120
he'd get denied.

11:58.120 --> 12:00.040
If you want,
I can call Donny at the bank

12:00.040 --> 12:01.620
and ask him
to straighten it out.

12:01.620 --> 12:02.880
[ Gags ]

12:02.880 --> 12:04.790
Delilah?

12:04.790 --> 12:05.790
Here.

12:09.170 --> 12:10.670
Are you okay?

12:10.670 --> 12:12.420
[ Sniffles ]

12:12.420 --> 12:14.620
I'm not okay.

12:14.620 --> 12:16.040
I'm pregnant.

12:16.040 --> 12:17.790
♪♪

12:17.790 --> 12:19.380
It's Jon's,
and the kids don't know,

12:19.380 --> 12:20.500
so please don't tell them,

12:20.500 --> 12:23.120
because with everything
they're going through,

12:23.120 --> 12:24.960
it's just --
No, I won't. I won't.

12:24.960 --> 12:26.790
[ Sighs ]

12:26.790 --> 12:28.580
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:31.710 --> 12:34.790
But this is a good thing,
right?

12:34.790 --> 12:35.960
Isn't it?

12:35.960 --> 12:37.290
[ Scoffs ]

12:37.290 --> 12:39.500
Yeah, I know
what you're thinking.

12:39.500 --> 12:41.790
It's a miracle baby.

12:41.790 --> 12:43.790
[ Toilet flushes ]

12:43.790 --> 12:45.790
[ Cries ]
No. I --

12:45.790 --> 12:47.120
I am a widow.

12:47.120 --> 12:49.170
I'm a widow,
and my husband just died,

12:49.170 --> 12:52.040
and I have
two grieving children.

12:52.040 --> 12:53.500
And the idea that Jon's
gonna live again

12:53.500 --> 12:54.500
through this baby

12:54.500 --> 12:56.330
is just not true because...

12:59.080 --> 13:02.540
The fact is, Jon is dead.

13:02.540 --> 13:04.500
[ Breathes deeply ]

13:04.500 --> 13:08.750
I'm not sure I'm ready to --
to do this alone.

13:08.750 --> 13:12.580
♪♪

13:12.580 --> 13:15.000
So...
[chuckles nervously]

13:15.000 --> 13:20.040
how's your dad and,
um [chuckles] Angie?

13:20.040 --> 13:22.330
Dad's good.

13:22.330 --> 13:23.250
They're good.

13:23.250 --> 13:25.580
Good. Good.

13:25.580 --> 13:27.080
Your Aunt Janet
showed me a picture

13:27.080 --> 13:28.880
of the four of you
visiting her on The Cape.

13:28.880 --> 13:30.170
Mom,
we're not doing this.

13:33.170 --> 13:34.420
Doing what?

13:34.420 --> 13:37.290
I-I was --
I was just being nice.

13:37.290 --> 13:39.380
You drove 45 minutes

13:39.380 --> 13:41.920
to tell me about a picture
you saw on Facebook?

13:41.920 --> 13:43.290
No.

13:43.290 --> 13:44.580
I drove 45 minutes

13:44.580 --> 13:47.040
to see a restaurant
I saw on Facebook.

13:47.040 --> 13:50.460
Honey, I am so proud of
my little girl.

13:50.460 --> 13:53.290
This place is just...

13:53.290 --> 13:54.670
It's fantastic.

13:58.290 --> 14:00.540
Well, yeah, it will be.

14:00.540 --> 14:01.830
I'm sorry I didn't call.

14:01.830 --> 14:03.000
I've just been crazy busy --

14:03.000 --> 14:05.000
I just wish that
you would've told me sooner

14:05.000 --> 14:06.620
'cause I could've
at least helped you

14:06.620 --> 14:08.460
find a better contractor,
so...

14:08.460 --> 14:09.420
[ Tools clatter ]

14:11.960 --> 14:13.330
Eddie:
All right, the Theo Bible.

14:13.330 --> 14:15.120
Who's taking food?
I am.

14:15.120 --> 14:16.960
I eat food. Food is easy.
I got food.

14:16.960 --> 14:18.580
Great.
He's pretty simple.

14:18.580 --> 14:20.170
Minimal gluten, no sugar.

14:20.170 --> 14:21.920
We try to keep him
off GMOs.

14:21.920 --> 14:23.710
Change of plans --
you're on food.

14:23.710 --> 14:25.330
Okay, next up, hygiene.

14:25.330 --> 14:27.290
Change of plans --
I'm back on food.

14:27.290 --> 14:29.040
No, tiny balls --
that's your department.

14:29.040 --> 14:31.000
Uh, how involved are we
with shower time?

14:31.000 --> 14:32.210
Turn it on,
you turn it off.

14:32.210 --> 14:33.790
Anything in between,
you are not involved with.

14:33.790 --> 14:35.120
I'm back on hygiene.

14:35.120 --> 14:36.670
By the way, his bath time
is during the show...

14:36.670 --> 14:38.000
Oh, stop!
...so have fun
with that.

14:38.000 --> 14:39.380
Uh-huh, uh-huh.
Gang.

14:39.380 --> 14:40.830
Next up.
Mm-hmm.

14:40.830 --> 14:42.290
[ Clears throat ]

14:42.290 --> 14:44.120
Okay, he doesn't get them
every night,

14:44.120 --> 14:45.620
but night terrors.

14:45.620 --> 14:47.500
Night...terrors?

14:47.500 --> 14:48.750
Wh--
That's really a thing?

14:48.750 --> 14:50.250
Yeah, it's basically
nightmares.

14:50.250 --> 14:51.330
Only much, much worse.

14:51.330 --> 14:52.790
It's kind of like

14:52.790 --> 14:53.710
a 7-year-old kid's version
of sleepwalking

14:53.710 --> 14:55.380
but with screaming.

14:55.380 --> 14:57.210
He's gonna be...

14:57.210 --> 14:58.290
looking at you.

14:58.290 --> 14:59.710
He'll be talking,

14:59.710 --> 15:01.580
but he's not talking
to you.

15:01.580 --> 15:02.750
Because of
all the screaming.

15:03.620 --> 15:04.880
So, don't let him
go to sleep.

15:04.880 --> 15:06.000
Got it.

15:06.000 --> 15:07.830
Do we?
Do we got it?

15:07.830 --> 15:09.420
[ Door buzzes,
knock on door ]

15:09.420 --> 15:10.620
Just read this.

15:10.620 --> 15:12.500
The last section
is self-explanatory.

15:12.830 --> 15:14.960
Hey.

15:14.960 --> 15:16.750
You wanted to enjoy
every moment of life, right?

15:16.750 --> 15:18.330
[ Door opens ]
Theo: Dad!

15:18.330 --> 15:19.540
[ Theo laughs ]
Here comes some life.

15:19.540 --> 15:20.830
And he's wearing a cape!

15:20.830 --> 15:23.210
Maggie: Yeah, he is!
Wow, cool!

15:23.210 --> 15:24.620
Oh, awesome cape, man.

15:24.620 --> 15:26.420
You know how soft
this couch is?

15:26.420 --> 15:28.750
[ Grunting ]

15:28.750 --> 15:30.330
[ Laughs ]

15:33.380 --> 15:41.330
♪♪

15:41.330 --> 15:49.330
♪♪

15:49.330 --> 15:57.040
♪♪

15:57.040 --> 15:59.040
[ Sighs ]

16:02.040 --> 16:04.380
[ Sighs ]

16:04.380 --> 16:06.670
Thanks for that.

16:06.670 --> 16:12.210
♪♪

16:12.210 --> 16:18.000
♪♪

16:18.000 --> 16:20.580
What is this?

16:20.580 --> 16:23.170
I should've given you this
sooner.

16:23.170 --> 16:25.460
It's from Jon.

16:25.460 --> 16:27.250
What do you mean,
from Jon?

16:27.250 --> 16:34.080
♪♪

16:34.080 --> 16:40.670
♪♪

16:40.670 --> 16:42.920
How --
How long have you had this?

16:42.920 --> 16:46.540
♪♪

16:46.540 --> 16:48.080
How could you
keep this from me?

16:48.080 --> 16:49.330
♪♪

16:49.330 --> 16:51.500
Answer me!
I'm sorry.

16:51.500 --> 16:52.920
You're sorry?
I trusted you.

16:52.920 --> 16:54.790
Jon trusted you.
No, no. You --
You don't understand.

16:54.790 --> 16:57.380
My kids think their dad left
without saying goodbye.

16:57.380 --> 17:00.080
[ Echoing ]
You let them believe that!
You don't understand.

17:00.080 --> 17:01.000
Get out of my house!

17:01.000 --> 17:02.540
You don't understand --

17:02.540 --> 17:04.830
Get out of here!
Get out!

17:04.830 --> 17:06.710
Get out of my house!
Ashley: I'm so sorry.

17:06.710 --> 17:08.620
♪♪

17:10.120 --> 17:11.620
[ Normal voice ] Hey.

17:11.620 --> 17:12.540
You heading out?

17:14.120 --> 17:16.250
Yeah.

17:16.250 --> 17:17.330
I'll see you tomorrow.

17:17.330 --> 17:21.000
♪♪

17:21.000 --> 17:23.330
I really like
this texture,

17:23.330 --> 17:27.080
but this is
a more inviting color.

17:27.080 --> 17:28.830
Shelly: No.

17:28.830 --> 17:30.790
Listen,
Rome mentioned that

17:30.790 --> 17:32.960
he stopped directing
those commercials

17:32.960 --> 17:34.670
and is now writing.

17:34.670 --> 17:35.540
Fun.

17:37.170 --> 17:39.210
If Rome and I
have learned anything

17:39.210 --> 17:40.880
these last few months,

17:40.880 --> 17:43.210
it's that sometimes
you have to live your life

17:43.210 --> 17:44.880
the way you want to.

17:44.880 --> 17:46.170
Well, we're not making
any decisions right now.

17:46.170 --> 17:47.790
No, we're not.

17:47.790 --> 17:50.290
It's just that starting
a restaurant isn't cheap.

17:50.290 --> 17:51.830
It takes money,
and lots of it.

17:51.830 --> 17:54.120
I-I am aware, Mother.

17:54.120 --> 17:56.420
Oh, luckily,
I have a little to spare.

17:56.420 --> 17:57.790
[ Scoffs ]

17:57.790 --> 18:00.710
And there it is.

18:00.710 --> 18:02.500
[ Exhales sharply ]

18:02.500 --> 18:04.460
Like --
We don't need your money.

18:04.460 --> 18:05.830
Thank you.

18:05.830 --> 18:07.790
It's not just about money,
sweetheart.

18:07.790 --> 18:09.710
Running a restaurant
is tough by yourself.

18:09.710 --> 18:11.920
I already have a partner.
Well...

18:11.920 --> 18:13.080
One who I trust

18:13.080 --> 18:14.960
and who is always there
for me.

18:17.040 --> 18:19.330
It's just...

18:19.330 --> 18:20.880
It's just that
you're so talented.
Mom.

18:20.880 --> 18:22.540
And -- And you deserve
a restaurant

18:22.540 --> 18:24.120
that actually succeeds.

18:24.120 --> 18:25.750
And it will.

18:39.000 --> 18:41.330
Shelly: So, what's
your movie about?

18:41.330 --> 18:44.420
Well,
still circling a few ideas.

18:44.420 --> 18:46.500
You know
I am your biggest fan.

18:46.500 --> 18:49.170
I watched all "The Bachelor"
last season

18:49.170 --> 18:52.040
just to see
your soda commercials.
[ Chuckles ]

18:52.040 --> 18:53.500
Your secret's safe
with me.

18:53.500 --> 18:55.330
Well, they -- they say

18:55.330 --> 18:58.670
you should write
what you know, so...

18:58.670 --> 19:00.040
I'm thinking
there's a movie about

19:00.040 --> 19:01.290
a group of friends.

19:01.290 --> 19:02.670
Hmm...

19:02.670 --> 19:06.040
[ Tape ripping ]

19:06.040 --> 19:08.460
Oh, my God!
Shelly,
what are you doing?!

19:08.460 --> 19:10.330
Oh!
You put that back.

19:10.330 --> 19:11.670
Am I finally
gonna be a Nana?

19:11.670 --> 19:12.920
[ Stammers ]
You like "Nana," right?

19:12.920 --> 19:14.170
It's just that "Grammy"
just feels like

19:14.170 --> 19:15.040
I'm trying too hard and --

19:15.040 --> 19:16.710
It's not
what you think it is.

19:16.710 --> 19:17.960
[ Whispering ]
It's for a friend.

19:17.960 --> 19:19.080
[ Whispering ]
If it's for a friend,

19:19.080 --> 19:20.710
why are we whispering?

19:20.710 --> 19:21.790
[ Normal voice ]
Gina's pregnant.

19:21.790 --> 19:23.120
How far along is she?

19:23.120 --> 19:24.750
Oh, that explains her attitude
at the restaurant.

19:24.750 --> 19:26.120
Shelly.

19:26.120 --> 19:28.000
Gina is not pregnant.

19:28.000 --> 19:29.710
We're not even
thinking about it, okay?

19:29.710 --> 19:30.710
Wait, Rome.

19:30.710 --> 19:33.120
Come on.
What's going on?

19:33.120 --> 19:37.330
We're...
not thinking about it.

19:39.330 --> 19:42.210
I am just a little.

19:42.210 --> 19:43.500
You want kids.

19:43.500 --> 19:46.330
No, it's --

19:46.330 --> 19:47.500
For a second,

19:47.500 --> 19:49.540
I thought
that Gina was pregnant,

19:49.540 --> 19:51.170
and it made me think...

19:51.170 --> 19:54.710
it's not that I want kids.

19:54.710 --> 19:59.080
It's just that
I don't not want kids.

19:59.080 --> 20:01.330
Then tell her that.

20:01.330 --> 20:04.080
You and Gina will make
the most amazing parents.

20:04.080 --> 20:05.170
It's not that simple.

20:05.170 --> 20:06.830
Gina's got a lot on her plate
right now

20:06.830 --> 20:08.120
with the new restaurant.
Oh, come on.

20:08.120 --> 20:09.210
I just quit my job!
So?

20:09.210 --> 20:10.580
Shelly.

20:10.580 --> 20:12.080
♪♪

20:12.080 --> 20:16.250
I will talk to Gina
when the time is right,

20:16.250 --> 20:18.790
and you have to promise me

20:18.790 --> 20:20.920
that you will not
say a word to her.

20:20.920 --> 20:24.880
[ Sighs ]

20:24.880 --> 20:26.170
Okay.

20:26.170 --> 20:29.000
Okay, I promise.

20:29.000 --> 20:30.620
But when the time is right,

20:30.620 --> 20:32.290
you talk to her
about the baby.

20:32.290 --> 20:33.750
I'm gonna talk to her
about the lighting.

20:33.750 --> 20:35.500
I mean, honestly.

20:35.500 --> 20:38.330
L.E.D.s -- just everyone
will look blue.

20:38.330 --> 20:40.620
[ Electricity humming ]

20:45.710 --> 20:47.790
Whoo! Yeah!

20:49.580 --> 20:50.880
[ Microphone feedback ]

20:50.880 --> 20:52.920
Yeah.

20:52.920 --> 20:53.960
Cory: Eddie?

20:53.960 --> 20:56.080
Is that you?

20:56.080 --> 20:58.580
Oh, man, I never thought
I'd see you again.

20:58.580 --> 21:00.790
Cory, talk about a blast
from the past, right?

21:00.790 --> 21:02.670
Yeah, my client's
headlining tonight.

21:04.500 --> 21:06.000
Damn!

21:06.000 --> 21:08.620
I remember when you flamed out
at the "Sundown" tour.

21:08.620 --> 21:10.420
That performance
in Pittsburgh, whoo!

21:10.420 --> 21:11.830
Legendary.

21:11.830 --> 21:13.460
They ever let you back
in a Radisson after that?

21:13.460 --> 21:14.960
Ha!

21:17.380 --> 21:19.670
Maggie: Aah, oh, no!

21:19.670 --> 21:21.580
That's the third time
that's happened.

21:21.580 --> 21:22.880
Hey, why don't you
put it in my bag?

21:22.880 --> 21:24.710
Don't you want to feel the sun
on your face?

21:24.710 --> 21:26.830
The rule is
if I'm in the sun,

21:26.830 --> 21:29.620
I have to either be in my hat
or wearing SPF 50.

21:29.620 --> 21:30.710
All right, you know,

21:30.710 --> 21:32.420
some rules
are made to be broken.

21:32.420 --> 21:33.500
No, they're not.

21:33.500 --> 21:34.920
Then they
wouldn't be rules.

21:34.920 --> 21:36.620
Huh.

21:36.620 --> 21:39.000
Touché, kid.

21:39.000 --> 21:39.750
[ Ducks quacking ]

21:39.750 --> 21:41.040
Hey!

21:41.040 --> 21:42.330
Look! Ooh!

21:42.330 --> 21:43.750
You know what?

21:43.750 --> 21:44.750
Let's go feed the ducks.

21:46.670 --> 21:47.880
Are you kidding me?

21:47.880 --> 21:49.210
You don't like ducks?

21:49.210 --> 21:50.620
Every kid likes ducks.

21:50.620 --> 21:52.080
You're not
supposed to feed them.

21:52.080 --> 21:53.170
Bread makes them gain weight,

21:53.170 --> 21:54.580
and if they gain weight,

21:54.580 --> 21:56.080
they get this thing called
"angel wing."

21:56.080 --> 21:57.880
Then they can't fly.

21:57.880 --> 22:00.420
I can't feed the ducks
because I like the ducks.

22:00.420 --> 22:03.580
Okay. All right.

22:03.580 --> 22:05.670
You make a solid argument
for the ducks,

22:05.670 --> 22:07.960
but surely
you can take off the hat

22:07.960 --> 22:09.830
just for, like,
10 minutes.

22:09.830 --> 22:10.920
No?

22:10.920 --> 22:13.080
All right.

22:13.080 --> 22:15.040
Well [sighs]

22:15.040 --> 22:16.830
then I guess you're just gonna
have to catch me!

22:16.830 --> 22:18.380
Ha ha!

22:18.380 --> 22:21.000
[ Laughing ]
Hey! Hey, give it back!
Whoo!

22:21.000 --> 22:23.620
[ Both laughing, grunting ]

22:23.620 --> 22:26.960
Hey, it's me.

22:26.960 --> 22:29.080
Listen, I, uh...

22:29.080 --> 22:30.830
I need your help with something.

22:30.830 --> 22:32.250
It's a big ask,

22:32.250 --> 22:36.170
so I totally get it
if the answer's no.

22:36.170 --> 22:39.790
[ Breathing sharply ]

22:39.790 --> 22:42.670
I need a ride to my, uh --
to my OB's office.

22:42.670 --> 22:45.670
They said that
after the procedure,

22:45.670 --> 22:47.500
I can't drive myself home.

22:47.500 --> 22:50.080
♪♪

22:50.080 --> 22:53.290
[ Exhales deeply ]

22:53.290 --> 22:56.210
Whatever you need.

22:56.210 --> 22:57.790
Okay.

22:57.790 --> 23:02.080
♪♪

23:02.080 --> 23:02.880
[ Exhales deeply ]

23:07.120 --> 23:09.000
Gina,
this chili is divine.

23:09.000 --> 23:10.620
Thanks.

23:10.620 --> 23:11.920
With just a little less
jalapeño,

23:11.920 --> 23:13.000
it'd be great
for your kids' menu.

23:13.000 --> 23:16.620
Um, I suppose.

23:16.620 --> 23:19.040
I mean, we haven't
worked on the specifics.

23:19.040 --> 23:21.000
Oh, of course.
I'm just thinking ahead.

23:21.000 --> 23:22.960
Shelly, can I help you
with that cornbread?

23:22.960 --> 23:24.710
Yeah, sure.

23:24.710 --> 23:26.040
Rome: Thank you.

23:26.040 --> 23:27.540
♪♪

23:27.540 --> 23:28.670
[ Whispering ]
Can you please stop?

23:28.670 --> 23:29.580
[ Whispering ]
Show her the hat.

23:29.580 --> 23:30.500
Shut it down.

23:32.250 --> 23:34.170
Listen, I know you think
you know everything,

23:34.170 --> 23:36.290
but there are some things
that even you do not know.

23:36.290 --> 23:37.080
[ Oven door clatters ]

23:37.080 --> 23:38.580
Who's hungry?

23:41.580 --> 23:49.540
♪♪

23:49.540 --> 23:57.460
♪♪

23:57.460 --> 23:59.750
Gary.

23:59.750 --> 24:01.170
Yeah?

24:01.170 --> 24:03.710
♪♪

24:03.710 --> 24:06.580
You're not saying
anything.

24:07.960 --> 24:09.420
Yeah.

24:12.080 --> 24:14.420
I just -- I don't want
to say the wrong thing.

24:16.080 --> 24:17.960
[ Sniffs ]

24:17.960 --> 24:18.790
♪♪

24:18.790 --> 24:22.250
Uh...

24:22.250 --> 24:25.210
[ Pen scratching ]

24:25.210 --> 24:26.750
Okay.

24:26.750 --> 24:27.750
Look.

24:30.880 --> 24:36.790
About -- About this or --
or anything else,

24:36.790 --> 24:38.880
I-I got your back, D, okay,

24:38.880 --> 24:41.420
until the end of time.

24:41.420 --> 24:43.330
[ Door opens ]

24:43.330 --> 24:46.080
♪♪

24:46.080 --> 24:47.620
Delilah Dixon?

24:47.620 --> 24:53.540
♪♪

24:53.540 --> 24:55.830
Should -- Should I --
No.

24:55.830 --> 24:57.620
♪♪

24:57.620 --> 25:00.290
[ Sighs ]

25:00.290 --> 25:02.080
I'll be right here.

25:02.080 --> 25:06.330
♪♪

25:06.330 --> 25:07.620
[ Sighs ]

25:10.540 --> 25:14.500
♪ Pray God, you can cope ♪

25:14.500 --> 25:18.380
♪ I stand outside ♪

25:18.380 --> 25:21.460
♪ This woman's work ♪

25:21.460 --> 25:23.380
♪ This woman's world ♪

25:23.380 --> 25:28.250
♪ Ooh, it's hard on the man ♪

25:28.250 --> 25:32.380
♪ Now his part is over ♪

25:32.380 --> 25:36.460
♪ Now starts the craft ♪

25:36.460 --> 25:43.120
♪ Of the Father ♪

25:43.120 --> 25:46.170
♪ I know you have a little life
in you yet ♪

25:46.170 --> 25:49.170
♪ I know you have
a lot of strength left ♪

25:49.170 --> 25:53.710
♪ I know you have a little life
in you yet ♪

25:53.710 --> 25:56.960
♪ I know you have
a lot of strength left ♪

25:56.960 --> 26:01.040
♪ I should be crying,
but I just can't let it show ♪

26:01.040 --> 26:04.710
♪ Should be hoping,
but I can't stop thinking ♪

26:04.710 --> 26:06.500
♪ Of all the things
I should've said ♪

26:06.500 --> 26:07.880
♪ But I never said ♪

26:07.880 --> 26:10.330
♪ All the things
we should've said done ♪

26:10.330 --> 26:12.040
♪ But we never did ♪

26:12.040 --> 26:13.880
♪ And all the things
I should've given ♪

26:13.880 --> 26:15.290
♪ But I didn't ♪

26:15.290 --> 26:20.330
♪ Oh, oh, my darling ♪

26:20.330 --> 26:24.000
♪ Make it go ♪

26:24.000 --> 26:28.000
♪ Make it go away ♪

26:28.000 --> 26:33.580
♪♪

26:33.580 --> 26:35.330
[ Door opens ]
♪ Give me ♪

26:35.330 --> 26:40.580
♪ These moments back ♪

26:40.580 --> 26:44.170
♪ Give them back ♪

26:44.170 --> 26:45.540
♪ To me ♪

26:45.540 --> 26:48.120
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

26:48.120 --> 26:51.210
♪ Give me that ♪

26:51.210 --> 26:55.620
♪ Little kiss ♪

26:55.620 --> 26:58.920
♪ Give me your ♪

27:00.420 --> 27:02.170
[ Door opens ]
♪ Hands ♪

27:02.170 --> 27:05.920
♪ I know you have a little life
in you yet ♪

27:05.920 --> 27:09.790
♪ I know you have
a lot of strength left ♪

27:09.790 --> 27:13.380
♪ I know you have a little life
in you yet ♪

27:13.380 --> 27:16.620
♪ I know you have
a lot of strength left ♪

27:16.620 --> 27:20.500
♪ I should be crying,
but I just can't let it show ♪

27:40.290 --> 27:42.830
I couldn't do it.

27:42.830 --> 27:51.170
♪♪

27:51.170 --> 27:54.040
[ Exhales sharply ]

27:54.040 --> 27:56.420
♪♪

27:56.420 --> 28:00.000
Well, uh...

28:00.000 --> 28:02.210
if you think
that you're doing this alone,

28:02.210 --> 28:03.880
you're wrong.

28:03.880 --> 28:06.380
♪♪

28:06.380 --> 28:08.540
Especially
the "eating for two" part.

28:08.540 --> 28:12.540
I am down to gain
some serious sympathy weight.

28:12.540 --> 28:14.290
Uh, what do you say

28:14.290 --> 28:16.960
we plow through
some chicken and waffles?

28:16.960 --> 28:19.250
Your treat.
[ Laughing ] What?

28:19.250 --> 28:21.120
I seem to have
forgotten my wallet.

28:21.120 --> 28:23.080
[ Both laugh ]

28:23.080 --> 28:24.500
[ Sighs ]

28:24.500 --> 28:27.040
♪♪

28:27.040 --> 28:28.580
Boom! Yes!

28:28.580 --> 28:32.000
5:00 on...the dot.

28:32.000 --> 28:33.710
Crushing it.

28:33.710 --> 28:35.710
Whatever errand
you had to run, Gary,

28:35.710 --> 28:36.500
I am so sorry,

28:36.500 --> 28:38.000
because you are missing out

28:38.000 --> 28:40.040
on some
celiac-friendly pasta.

28:40.040 --> 28:43.500
Eddie: All right, it's time
for me to go to the gig.

28:43.500 --> 28:45.380
Are you sure
you have to go?

28:45.380 --> 28:47.000
Yeah,
I'm sorry, bud.

28:47.000 --> 28:49.420
I wish
I could take you with me.

28:49.420 --> 28:50.880
[ Chuckles ]
Believe me.

28:50.880 --> 28:54.080
I don't know if I'm gonna
be able to fall asleep

28:54.080 --> 28:55.080
without you here.

28:55.080 --> 28:58.380
♪♪

28:58.380 --> 29:00.750
[ Sighs ]

29:00.750 --> 29:02.080
It's okay, bud.

29:02.080 --> 29:06.460
♪♪

29:06.460 --> 29:08.330
Everybody gets scared
sometimes.

29:10.170 --> 29:13.540
But just because
you're scared,

29:13.540 --> 29:16.710
it doesn't mean
you shouldn't do it.

29:16.710 --> 29:20.080
Sometimes that's exactly
the reason why you should.

29:20.080 --> 29:21.080
[ Chuckles ]

29:21.080 --> 29:22.960
I love you, Dad.

29:22.960 --> 29:25.620
♪♪

29:25.620 --> 29:27.290
I love you, too, bud.

29:27.290 --> 29:32.170
♪♪

29:33.460 --> 29:35.500
Shelly: Yeah, I-I read
the most fascinating article

29:35.500 --> 29:37.000
in The Atlantic
the other day.

29:37.000 --> 29:40.040
Apparently, children with
stay-at-home dads

29:40.040 --> 29:42.080
is on the rise.

29:42.080 --> 29:43.080
Watch it, Mom.

29:43.080 --> 29:45.460
What?
It was a great read.

29:45.460 --> 29:46.960
Uh, I've told you
since I was 10

29:46.960 --> 29:48.420
that I do not
want to have kids,

29:48.420 --> 29:49.670
and that answer
has not changed.

29:49.670 --> 29:51.670
Not when I turned 30,

29:51.670 --> 29:53.040
not when Rome and I
got married,

29:53.040 --> 29:54.330
and certainly
not in the middle

29:54.330 --> 29:57.250
of opening a restaurant.

29:57.250 --> 30:00.580
Perhaps you two
should talk.

30:00.580 --> 30:02.710
Enough!

30:02.710 --> 30:05.460
Enough with
the passive aggression,

30:05.460 --> 30:08.040
and stop it
with all your questions.

30:08.040 --> 30:09.420
Gina --
No, just because

30:09.420 --> 30:11.170
you think
that we should have kids

30:11.170 --> 30:13.880
does not mean
that you can come into our house

30:13.880 --> 30:16.710
and meddle with
our marriage, our bond.

30:16.710 --> 30:17.790
It's bad enough

30:17.790 --> 30:19.500
that you wrecked
your marriage with Dad,

30:19.500 --> 30:20.920
but please don't
try to wreck mine.

30:25.960 --> 30:27.500
Well, Rome.

30:29.040 --> 30:30.880
Regina.

30:30.880 --> 30:33.620
This has been
an eventful evening,

30:33.620 --> 30:35.790
but I think it is best
that I go.

30:44.420 --> 30:45.790
[ Exhales deeply ]

30:45.790 --> 30:47.210
♪♪

30:47.210 --> 30:50.040
[ Door slams ]

30:50.040 --> 30:51.750
Well...

30:51.750 --> 30:53.750
that happened.

30:53.750 --> 30:56.250
You know
you want to go.

30:59.170 --> 31:01.080
She's your mom.

31:02.830 --> 31:04.750
You should go.
[ Sniffles ]

31:04.750 --> 31:09.880
♪♪

31:09.880 --> 31:11.710
Mom.

31:11.710 --> 31:12.790
Wait, I'm sorry. I --

31:12.790 --> 31:14.790
I know you may not
appreciate my advice,

31:14.790 --> 31:16.290
but I am your mother.

31:16.290 --> 31:17.420
[ Elevator bell dings ]

31:19.500 --> 31:24.170
♪♪

31:24.170 --> 31:25.670
You were right.

31:25.670 --> 31:27.620
My marriage didn't work

31:27.620 --> 31:30.580
because I didn't see
what was right in front of me.

31:30.580 --> 31:32.620
You may think
that you and Rome

31:32.620 --> 31:34.670
have a bulletproof
relationship,

31:34.670 --> 31:36.830
but so did I.

31:36.830 --> 31:42.540
♪♪

31:42.540 --> 31:48.210
♪♪

31:48.210 --> 31:50.080
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:50.080 --> 31:51.540
Cory: Eddie.

31:51.540 --> 31:53.380
This is my client KC.

31:53.380 --> 31:54.330
He's headliner tonight.

31:54.330 --> 31:56.750
Oh, hey!
Great to meet you.

31:56.750 --> 31:59.000
Man, I am legit psyched
right now.

31:59.000 --> 32:01.620
My senior yearbook quote
was a Ferns lyric.

32:01.620 --> 32:02.960
No joke, man.

32:02.960 --> 32:04.540
"You can't
set the world on fire

32:04.540 --> 32:06.080
if you don't have
any gas."

32:06.080 --> 32:07.290
Yeah, you know it, man.
Yeah, of course.

32:07.290 --> 32:08.460
You really were a fan.
Wow.
Yeah, dude,

32:08.460 --> 32:09.960
back in the day,
you were an animal.

32:09.960 --> 32:10.960
[ Laughs ]

32:10.960 --> 32:11.920
Uh, so,
what's been going on?

32:11.920 --> 32:12.750
Where you been going up?

32:12.750 --> 32:15.380
Well, just here mostly.

32:15.380 --> 32:16.960
[ Bottles thud ]
Waitress: Here you go, KC.
Thank you.

32:16.960 --> 32:18.330
I got to go,

32:18.330 --> 32:20.170
but Cory said you're
working on some new stuff.

32:20.170 --> 32:21.330
That's killer, man.

32:21.330 --> 32:22.830
I'm excited to see
what you got.

32:22.830 --> 32:23.880
Thanks, man.
Yeah.

32:26.460 --> 32:30.170
[ Breathes deeply ]

32:30.170 --> 32:34.920
♪♪

32:34.920 --> 32:37.000
Man: [ Echoing ] And now
please welcome to the stage

32:37.000 --> 32:38.750
The Red Ferns!

32:38.750 --> 32:41.080
[ Guitar riff plays ]

32:41.080 --> 32:48.000
♪♪

32:48.000 --> 32:53.290
♪♪

32:53.580 --> 32:55.670
No, Donny,
you're not hearing me.

32:55.670 --> 32:57.710
He doesn't have a loan
on any personal property.

32:57.710 --> 32:59.880
The house was paid off
a long time ago.

32:59.880 --> 33:01.750
Are you saying he took out
another mortgage?

33:01.750 --> 33:03.620
Wh-- But wouldn't
he need her signature?

33:05.250 --> 33:07.790
Are you sure?
[ Car alarm chirps ]

33:07.790 --> 33:09.380
He has all that stuff
sent to the office,

33:09.380 --> 33:10.380
and we've never
received notice.

33:14.830 --> 33:16.210
Damn it.
I'll call you back.

33:18.420 --> 33:21.080
How -- How did
your secret errand go?

33:21.080 --> 33:23.330
[ Television playing
indistinctly in background ]

33:23.330 --> 33:26.460
Surprisingly okay.
Mm.

33:26.460 --> 33:28.460
Gotta get
to Eddie's gig.

33:28.460 --> 33:30.330
And you smell like
maple syrup

33:30.330 --> 33:31.830
because...?

33:31.830 --> 33:35.330
Uh, that, I'm afraid...

33:35.330 --> 33:37.120
I am not at liberty
to discuss that.

33:37.120 --> 33:38.290
[ Keys jingle ]

33:38.290 --> 33:39.880
[ Sighs ] Okay --

33:39.880 --> 33:42.420
Theo: Get away from me!

33:42.420 --> 33:43.880
The thing.
Night terror.

33:43.880 --> 33:45.540
They're too heavy!
They won't be able to fly!

33:45.540 --> 33:46.460
Oh, hey.

33:46.460 --> 33:47.620
Remember we didn't

33:47.620 --> 33:49.250
actually end up
feeding the ducks.

33:49.250 --> 33:50.580
Get them away from me!

33:50.580 --> 33:51.620
Remember he said
don't talk to him?
Yeah.

33:51.620 --> 33:52.540
It's okay, Khan.

33:52.540 --> 33:54.380
Please, please!
It can't eat it!

33:54.380 --> 33:55.880
[ Cellphone vibrating ]
Wait.

33:55.880 --> 33:57.290
Are you seriously gonna
answer that right now?

33:57.290 --> 33:58.500
Oh, what are you doing?

33:58.500 --> 34:00.170
Just answer the damn phone.

34:00.170 --> 34:02.420
Well, don't swear
in front of the child.

34:02.420 --> 34:03.500
Oh, is that
a priority --
Please, no!

34:03.500 --> 34:04.500
Please!

34:04.500 --> 34:06.120
Hello?
Hey, bud, it's okay.

34:06.120 --> 34:07.710
[ Snootily ] Oh!
Hello, Edward!

34:07.710 --> 34:09.000
Get them away from me!

34:09.000 --> 34:10.120
[ Normal voice ] So nice of you
to call and check in.

34:10.120 --> 34:11.120
How's things?

34:11.120 --> 34:12.380
Uh, not good.

34:12.380 --> 34:13.330
Not good at all, man.

34:13.330 --> 34:14.580
Theo: Stop feeding them.

34:14.580 --> 34:16.170
Look, I think
I need you here, Gary.

34:16.170 --> 34:17.420
I-I'm sort of
freaking out.

34:17.420 --> 34:19.460
Oh, you're freaking out?
He's freaking out?

34:19.460 --> 34:20.710
Theo: They're too heavy!
Listen, buddy,

34:20.710 --> 34:22.170
everything's
gonna be okay.

34:22.170 --> 34:23.500
No!
Aah!

34:23.500 --> 34:25.580
No.
I don't think so, man.

34:25.580 --> 34:27.040
[ Whispering ]
You're the psychologist.
What do we do?

34:27.040 --> 34:29.040
I don't -- This says
just to wait it out.

34:29.040 --> 34:30.880
Wait it out?
Yeah!
Theo: No!

34:30.880 --> 34:31.790
Eddie:
Gary, are you there?

34:31.790 --> 34:32.830
All right,
listen to me, man.

34:32.830 --> 34:33.960
I know it's been a while,

34:33.960 --> 34:35.330
but you've been on stage
hundreds of times, right?

34:35.330 --> 34:36.670
And -- And as frustrating
as it is

34:36.670 --> 34:37.920
for me to say this
with any sincerity,

34:37.920 --> 34:41.120
you did open for Kings of Leon,
right?

34:41.120 --> 34:44.830
That's just it.

34:44.830 --> 34:47.210
I...barely remember
any of that, man.

34:47.210 --> 34:49.080
I've...

34:49.080 --> 34:50.920
never performed sober
before.

34:50.920 --> 34:52.960
Oh...my God.

34:52.960 --> 34:55.000
Uh, okay, Ed.

34:55.000 --> 34:57.040
Uh, listen, buddy.

34:57.040 --> 34:58.330
What are you guys doing?

34:58.330 --> 35:01.080
Why'd you wake me?

35:01.080 --> 35:03.080
My bedtime is 8:00.

35:03.080 --> 35:07.000
Ed, hang on.

35:07.000 --> 35:09.000
We're coming over.

35:09.000 --> 35:11.420
Rome: Gina!

35:11.420 --> 35:13.210
We gotta go.

35:13.210 --> 35:15.380
He goes on stage
in less than a half-hour.

35:15.380 --> 35:16.960
Regina: Rome.
Yeah, babe?

35:16.960 --> 35:18.210
What is this?

35:20.170 --> 35:21.830
I bought that hat
because I --

35:21.830 --> 35:27.750
♪♪

35:27.750 --> 35:33.620
♪♪

35:33.620 --> 35:35.500
[ Voice breaking ]
What is this?

35:35.500 --> 35:36.670
[ Breathing shakily ]

35:40.330 --> 35:41.540
Gina, you have to know

35:41.540 --> 35:43.460
this had nothing to do
with you.

35:43.460 --> 35:44.960
How could you say this has
nothing to do with me?

35:44.960 --> 35:47.500
Because I love you.

35:47.500 --> 35:51.210
More than every single part
of my life combined.

35:51.210 --> 35:52.460
[ Inhales sharply ]

35:52.460 --> 35:55.170
We sat in that funeral
saying,

35:55.170 --> 35:57.080
"How did he not
tell Delilah?"

35:57.080 --> 35:58.830
[ Voice breaking ]
Oh, my God.
No, Gina, Gina.

35:58.830 --> 36:00.290
You don't --
You don't understand.

36:00.290 --> 36:02.000
No, I don't understand!

36:03.120 --> 36:08.040
How could I possibly
understand this?!

36:08.040 --> 36:10.710
[ Voice breaking ]
That's what I'm trying
to tell you, Gina.

36:13.830 --> 36:15.830
[ Crying ]
I don't understand it either.

36:17.460 --> 36:19.540
I don't.

36:21.040 --> 36:24.750
I have a great life.

36:24.750 --> 36:25.750
[ Sniffles ]

36:25.750 --> 36:30.380
But sometimes,
for some reason,

36:30.380 --> 36:33.040
I feel so sad.

36:35.420 --> 36:40.120
And I can't help but think
what if --

36:40.120 --> 36:42.790
what if this is the happiest
I'm ever gonna be?

36:42.790 --> 36:47.580
♪♪

36:47.580 --> 36:49.380
Okay.

36:51.750 --> 36:55.040
My turn.

36:55.040 --> 36:57.580
[ Sniffles ]

36:57.580 --> 37:01.880
And I need you
to listen to me.

37:01.880 --> 37:03.750
I need you to hear me.

37:03.750 --> 37:05.880
♪♪

37:05.880 --> 37:08.040
You are not
the best part of my life.

37:08.040 --> 37:11.830
You are my life.

37:11.830 --> 37:14.330
And I will not lose you.

37:14.330 --> 37:20.620
[ Crying ]

37:20.620 --> 37:21.960
[ Sniffles ]

37:21.960 --> 37:25.420
♪♪

37:25.420 --> 37:28.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

37:28.250 --> 37:30.040
Gary: Knock, knock!

37:30.040 --> 37:33.710
Somebody order
a 50-pound scream machine?

37:33.710 --> 37:35.580
Hey.

37:37.620 --> 37:39.330
You know, you screamed
way more than Theo did.

37:39.330 --> 37:40.380
It was the eyes.

37:40.380 --> 37:41.540
They're so glassy.

37:41.540 --> 37:42.790
♪♪

37:42.790 --> 37:45.250
Theo:
We came to see your show.

37:45.250 --> 37:47.620
Are you okay, Dad?

37:47.620 --> 37:48.880
♪♪

37:48.880 --> 37:50.290
I'm great.

37:50.290 --> 37:52.790
I just, uh --

37:52.790 --> 37:55.170
I -- I'm just
a little scared to play.

37:55.170 --> 37:56.250
That's all.

37:56.250 --> 37:58.460
You know, Dad,

37:58.460 --> 37:59.580
just because you're scared

37:59.580 --> 38:01.460
doesn't mean
you shouldn't do it.

38:01.460 --> 38:02.960
[ Chuckles ]

38:02.960 --> 38:04.710
♪♪

38:04.710 --> 38:07.080
You're right, bud.

38:07.080 --> 38:08.750
You're absolutely right.

38:08.750 --> 38:10.710
♪♪

38:16.540 --> 38:18.120
[ Door closes ]

38:18.120 --> 38:25.580
♪♪

38:25.580 --> 38:33.000
♪♪

38:33.000 --> 38:40.250
♪♪

38:40.250 --> 38:48.790
♪♪

38:48.790 --> 38:57.290
♪♪

38:57.290 --> 38:59.290
Woman: And now,
please welcome to the stage

38:59.290 --> 39:01.710
Eddie Saville!

39:01.710 --> 39:03.420
[ Cheers and applause ]

39:03.420 --> 39:05.500
Gary: Let's do this!
Go, Dad! Whoo!

39:05.500 --> 39:10.540
[ Cheers and applause continue ]

39:10.540 --> 39:12.580
Hi.

39:12.580 --> 39:13.670
-Whoo!
-Yes!

39:13.670 --> 39:15.330
[ Audience murmurs ]

39:20.250 --> 39:22.290
This is called "Unexpected."

39:22.290 --> 39:23.620
[ Clears throat ]

39:23.620 --> 39:28.330
♪♪

39:28.330 --> 39:30.540
♪ This was unexpected ♪

39:30.540 --> 39:33.710
♪ If I blinked,
I'd have missed it ♪

39:33.710 --> 39:36.460
♪ Wasn't looking for the fall ♪

39:39.500 --> 39:42.210
♪ I was barely holding on ♪

39:42.210 --> 39:45.330
♪ The dreams
have come and gone ♪

39:45.330 --> 39:49.040
♪ Years went on
and stole it all ♪

39:49.040 --> 39:52.920
♪ And I go ♪

39:52.920 --> 39:59.330
♪ 'Round and around
like a satellite ♪

40:04.290 --> 40:10.250
♪ Looking for
somewhere to land ♪

40:11.540 --> 40:15.920
♪ We spend our whole lives ♪

40:15.920 --> 40:20.210
♪ Under the same sky ♪

40:20.210 --> 40:22.960
[ Cheers and applause ]

40:22.960 --> 40:25.580
♪ We never collide ♪

40:25.580 --> 40:27.420
KC:
How about another hand

40:27.420 --> 40:28.580
for my buddy Eddie Saville?

40:28.580 --> 40:30.290
♪ Under the same sky ♪

40:30.290 --> 40:31.790
Hey.
Hey, man.

40:31.790 --> 40:34.250
Thanks, guys. Thank you.

40:34.250 --> 40:37.170
♪ Then such a simple thing ♪

40:37.170 --> 40:39.580
♪ How everything changes ♪
Delilah: Hey.

40:39.580 --> 40:44.960
♪ And you're over the moon ♪

40:44.960 --> 40:46.210
I didn't think
you'd be here.

40:46.210 --> 40:47.250
♪ I'm over the moon ♪

40:47.250 --> 40:48.250
Of course.

40:48.250 --> 40:49.500
You're amazing.

40:49.500 --> 40:52.620
Listen.

40:52.620 --> 40:57.500
Even though
the baby isn't mine,

40:57.500 --> 41:00.580
I'm here for you

41:00.580 --> 41:02.670
whenever you need,
whatever you need.

41:02.670 --> 41:05.880
Even after everything
I said to you?

41:05.880 --> 41:08.750
Well, there's nothing
you can say to me

41:08.750 --> 41:11.830
that will change the fact
that I love you.

41:11.830 --> 41:13.880
I can't do this.

41:16.080 --> 41:17.250
I can't lie you.

41:17.250 --> 41:18.540
I...

41:18.540 --> 41:21.750
Jon and I, we weren't...

41:21.750 --> 41:24.830
we weren't
sleeping together.

41:24.830 --> 41:26.380
This is your baby.

41:26.380 --> 41:31.250
♪ We never collide ♪

41:31.250 --> 41:35.380
♪ Under the same sky ♪
It's just --
It's too much.

41:35.380 --> 41:38.080
And Sophie and Danny and Theo --
there's just --

41:38.080 --> 41:40.290
♪ Then such
a simple thing ♪
They would never --

41:40.290 --> 41:43.120
And Katherine --
we just we hurt too many people.

41:43.120 --> 41:44.120
No, I know.

41:44.120 --> 41:48.420
♪ Over the moon ♪

41:49.500 --> 41:51.250
The baby
has to be Jon's.

41:51.250 --> 41:55.290
♪ I'm over the moon ♪

41:58.500 --> 42:08.000
♪♪

42:08.000 --> 42:17.580
♪♪

42:17.580 --> 42:27.000
♪♪
